ce-transfer-credit-cards%5C%22%3Ebalance%20transfer%20credit%20cards%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Racking%20up%20a%20balance%20on%20your%20old%20credit%20card%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20popular%20way%20to%20manage%20debt%20is%20to%20transfer%20the%20balance%20on%20an%20existing%20credit%20card%20to%20a%20balance%20transfer%20credit%20card%20with%20a%20low%20or%200%25%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fwhat-is-apr%5C%22%3EAPR%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%200%25%20APR%20lasts%20for%20a%20short%20period%2C%20usually%20six%20to%2018%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20to%20keep%20an%20eye%20out%20for%20is%20to%20run%20up%20a%20new%20balance%20on%20your%20old%20card.%20After%20you've%20shifted%20your%20debt%20from%20one%20card%20to%20the%20other%2C%20you%20start%20using%20your%20old%20card.%20Before%20you%20know%20it%2C%20you%20now%20have%20twice%20as%20much%20debt.%20%26quot%3BI've%20seen%20this%20happen%20a%20ton%2C%20where%20someone%20will%20treat%20it%20like%20free%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Being%20unaware%20of%20the%20balance%20transfer%20fees%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20fail%20to%20consider%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fare-balance-transfers-worth-it%5C%22%3Ebalance%20transfer%20fees%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20getting%20a%20balance%20transfer%20card.%20Balance%20transfer%20fees%20are%20usually%20either%20a%20flat%20fee%20or%20a%20percentage%20of%20the%20transfer%20amount.%20If%20a%20percentage%2C%20it's%20typically%20between%203%25%20to%205%25%20of%20what%20you're%20moving%20to%20the%20new%20card.%20This%20is%20tacked%20on%20to%20your%20balance%20at%20the%20time%20of%20transfer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20sure%20it's%20financially%20worthwhile%2C%20run%20the%20numbers%20to%20see%20if%20it%20makes%20sense%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fhow-to-complete-balance-transfer%5C%22%3Etransfer%20the%20balance%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BCheck%20and%20see%20what%20you're%20going%20to%20pay%20in%20fees%20against%20how%20much%20you'll%20save%20in%20interest%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jack.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20you%20have%20a%20low%20balance%20or%20are%20almost%20done%20paying%20it%20off%2C%20moving%20your%20money%20might%20not%20make%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBalance%20Transfer%20Credit%20Cards%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fbest-cash-back-credit-cards%5C%22%3Ebest%20balance%20transfer%20credit%20cards%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20help%20you%20take%20control%20of%20your%20debt.%20Popular%20cards%20include%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fchase-freedom-unlimited-review%5C%22%3EChase%20Freedom%20Unlimited%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fwells-fargo-reflect-credit-card-review%5C%22%3EWells%20Fargo%20Reflect%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Not%20understanding%20that%20opening%20a%20new%20card%20will%20hurt%20your%20credit%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20open%20a%20new%20credit%20card%2C%20the%20creditor%20will%20pull%20hard%20on%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-score%2Fhow-to-get-free-credit-report%5C%22%3Ecredit%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Jack%20explains%20that%20it%20usually%20dings%20your%20score%20by%20five%20to%2010%20points.%20However%2C%20it%20can%20drop%20your%20score%20within%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20when%20you%20open%20a%20balance%20transfer%20credit%20card%2C%20your%20total%20credit%20limit%20will%20increase%2C%20lowering%20your%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-score%2Fcredit-utilization-ratio%5C%22%3E%20credit%20utilization%20ratio%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20can%20help%20your%20credit%20score%2C%20as%20the%20lower%20your%20credit%20usage%2C%20the%20better%20your%20score.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Not%20paying%20attention%20to%20the%20standard%20APR%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%200%25%20interest%20rate%20is%20what%20got%20you%20signed%20up%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20know%20the%20standard%20APR%20on%20your%20balance%20transfer%20credit%20card.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20perfect%20world%2C%20you'd%20pay%20off%20the%20balance%20before%20the%20standard%20rate%20kicks%20in%2C%20but%20you'll%20want%20to%20be%20clued%20in.%20Should%20you%20still%20have%20to%20pay%20off%20the%20card%20after%20the%20promo%20rate%20ends%2C%20you%20might%20pay%20more%20interest%20fees%20on%20the%20remaining%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20Neglecting%20to%20shop%20around%20for%20the%20best%20offer%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20with%20credit%20card%20debt%20will%20sometimes%20jump%20on%20the%20first%20credit%20card%20balance%20transfer%20offer%20they%20get.%20Instead%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20shop%20around%20for%20the%20best%20rates%20and%20offers.%20Jack%20explains%20that%20the%20fees%20and%20terms%20can%20vary%20from%20card%20to%20card.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20creditors%20might%20charge%20you%205%25%20to%20consolidate%20your%20debt%2C%20but%20the%20length%20of%20time%20will%20be%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20You%20might%20trade%20off%20a%20longer%20period%20for%20the%20low%20rate%20for%20a%20higher%20fee%2C%20or%20vice%20versa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E6.%20Forgetting%20to%20buffer%20in%20more%20expensive%20months%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJack%20explains%20that%20even%20if%20you%20have%2018%20months%20to%20pay%20off%20your%20balance%20before%20the%20interest-free%20period%20ends%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20factor%20in%20those%20months%20when%20your%20spending%20is%20higher%20than%20the%20norm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou'll%20need%20to%20factor%20in%20holidays%2C%20expenses%20like%20birthday